text: King of Italy Vittorio Emanuele III (also known as Re d'Italia Vittorio Emanuele III) is a 19th-century painted in oil by the italian painter Giuseppe Amisani, made in 1925, is kept in the Collezione Farnesina of foreign minister of the Italian government in Rome from 1925.Vittorio Emanuele III == Related pages == * Giuseppe Amisani ==References== ==Other websites== * * Vittorio Emanuele III Category:1920s paintings Category:Rome Category:Paintings by Giuseppe Amisani
title: King of Italy Vittorio Emanuele III (Amisani)
